data.title: Passport Acceptance at the Fullerton Public Library
data.text:
PHOTOS

Need a passport photo?

Our certified passport agents ensure your photo is taken with care and expertise. From infants to seniors, we've got you covered. No appointment needed,* just drop in any time up until 1 hour before closing. Get your convenient passport photo taken at our library today!

*Prices and availability subject to change.

*No appointment needed for photo service. Passport application acceptance requires an appointment.

PASSPORT ACCEPTANCE FACILITIES DO NOT PROCESS

THE DS-82 PASSPORT RENEWAL APPLICATION OR

ACCEPT APPOINTMENTS FOR THEIR USE

HOWEVER

Most adult renewals can be done by mail!

If you have a passport that has not been expired for more than 5 years (or is still valid) and you were at least 16 years old when it was issued,

you may be able to submit a self-service renewal.

Please visit the U.S. Department of State – Renew my US Passport page to see if you qualify for this service.

The Library thanks you for complying with the Code of Conduct.

Prohibited behavior includes, but is not limited to, interfering with another Library patron’s use of the Library and/or with the performance by Library staff of their duties, behaving in a manner which reasonably can be expected to disturb others, harassing or annoying others through noisy or boisterous activities, battery, verbal threats, abusive language, [and/or] offensive touching. Full details may be viewed here:

https://fullertonlibrary.org/code-of-conduct
